Love their happy hour
Wonderful food and service! So glad it's open again!
Awesome place to eat something when in a hurry. Their customer service is efficient, prices are convenient, good mood. Will visit here again
Great wine selection, very courteous wait staff, and delicious food (their burger is the best I've had). Definitely check it out.
Staff was very helpful and nice. The burger was absolutely delicious. The environment was well thought out as well
Absolutely fantastic. We went for Valentine’s Day. Cannot wait to go back.
It was ok, our waiter sounded like a used car salesman, but the place was over all ok. I wouldn't go back, it was a nice one and done stop.
Croquettes, shrimp, and duck are all to die for. Fantastique!
1st visit and I wasn't disappointed. Nice ambience and the food, presentation and quality was on point. Recommended!

Server called me honey several times and not in an endearing way. 🙄 (It's Ms. or madam.)  Portions were small next to what you're paying and I can only recommend eating here if it's curbside or delivery.

Great experience for my birthday dinner. Service was good and I loved everything I had. The igloos were a little wonky and I was not as warm as I would've liked but I would not deduct a star for that.
Great place overall, especially during COVID

Le Sud was the perfect place to propose to my girlfriend. I couldn't be happier with how it went! The staff was supportive, professional and the food was absolutely delicious. Le Sud delivered on all accounts, and went above and beyond to give us a magical night. What a remarkable experience!

This was our 2nd time here but first since they changed to a Mediterranean menu. It's still got a French flair but honestly,  I think the dishes are more imaginative now. They have several private, outdoor, enclosed cabanas with heaters inside and really everything you might need for minimum interaction with the waitstaff. I do wish the server had told us more about the food, he just kind of dropped it and ran but I get it, they are trying to mitigate exposure.There are minimums which they are great about telling you before you arrive. They are serious about covid guidelines and that was really important to me. We will definitely be back when snow falls, it will be like a reverse snow globe!
Outstanding dishes, and terrific social distancing in practice: personal “igloos” with individual heaters, Bluetooth speakers, and call buttons.
French food, mmm, quality stuff. The service was very kind and attentive. My apartment is far from here, so I can't visit often.
The food was lovely! They kept the doors open throughout dinner, (presumable for ventilation?) making for an uncomfortably chilly dining experience - at least until the wine kicked in!
Food, ambience and all the staff were great! Social distancing was in place and very accommodating to our needs and dietary restrictions. Drinks were also delicious!
Happy Hour is a STEAL and their burger is out of this world!

This place has a really really good happy hour. $6 drinks and $6 appetizers during the happy hour and been outstanding burger to say the least. I'd absolutely come back here the wine selection is very very good as well. And the service is outstanding.
One of my favorite locations for tasty french food. Good place to hang and eat some good food. I'll return with my friends. Prices were decent.
Healthy food.
Great all around, food, service, atmosphere and price, a delightful place to dine.
I just ordered the creme brûlée to carry out. Omg, this is the best of the best creme brûlée I ever had. Definitely I will come back to try the food here. Great atmosphere as well

Delicious! We started with a basil martini, Lillet away, steamed muscles, and bread. They all had their own points of brilliance but the basil martini really stood out as excellent, so there was another round of those. For the main course we enjoyed the cod as well as an excellent bone in pork chop, with frites. The pork chop could be a mainstay in any fine dining experience. Topped off with a well paired glass of wine to match the pork. Finished the night with a creme brûlée. Great dining experience, we will be back!
Great food, cocktails & service. Nice outdoor seating

Le Sud is a great place to eat, drink, and relax at. You can actually hear yourself talk since there's no loud music! There are tables for two people so if you come with just one other person it's comfortable. If you bring your family they've also got you covered. Lots of vegetarian options (pasta, vegetables, etc). The staff is nice and accommodating (if you have specific dietary needs). They really put time and effort into creating new and exciting dishes. This is a great location. I'll be coming back soon!
Everything was delicious, and staff is always top notch. Love it!
This place is amazing.
Place is adorable, food is delicious, service is friendly and attentive, love everything. So happy to have found a gem in Roscoe.
I had an amazing  at this spot. We enjoyed the fantastic atmosphere and the food. The staff are very personal. I am glad we ultimately decided to try this restaurant.
This spot is worth a try. They serve big portions for reasonable prices. Always well organized and with fantastic mood. Will come back again.
I prefer this place very much. It has a great mood. The food is splendid. the service is efficient and the team is friendly. The price is fair. I definitely recommend.
Very well kept and welcoming place. They serve generous meals and for affordable rates. We enjoyed the meals a lot and the staff were super attentive and explanatory. Highly recommended.
Excellent food, great atmosphere.  Will definitely be back.
Always awesome! Never a bad experience or meal

Lovely food in a relaxed, casual atmosphere.

The food and service never disappoint! We went for restaurant week this past visit and it's such an amazing deal. Le Sud also has a wonderful happy hour on the sidewalk patio in the warmer months, which is lovely!
One of the best meals I've ever had in Chicago. God bless French cuisine.
The quality keeps going down while the prices go up.
Good French menu with terrific service.  Sit outside on patio in the summer.
Try the Burger it's great and sit in the bar, sometimes there's a fight in the kitchen. Dinner and a show.
Outstanding service. The scallops, octopus and steak frites were incredible. Highly recommended.

So disappointed. Mushy-sloppy burger, rabbit stew had bones and nasty shredded meat, and cheese plate had almost no cheese and nut crumbs not whole nuts. ??? Every dish **way** over-salted.. almost inedible. Waiter disappeared for a looooong time. Ordered a bottle of wine  and they brought one glass instead. Waiter clueless about the wine selection.

Excellent food and service! Highly highly recommend!  We went there for dinner with a group of 5 (4 adults, 1 little one). We ordered apps, entrees and dessert, and everything was delicious: carrot appetizer, soup of the day (cheddar with tomato and potato), rabbit stew, trout, duck, chocolate mousse and raspberry amaretto sorbet. Everything tasted extremely fresh and homemade - nothing processed. Somehow they even managed to make the French fries with the kids entree taste superior to all other fries.  We also were happy to discover that we were on time for their Saturday Happy Hour special and ordered up the cocktail of the day: the black walnut old fashioned made with rum and black walnut bitters. It was strong but incredibly smooth. Changed the whole idea of old fashions for me.  Last but certainly not least, the service was excellent. Our server was very friendly, professional and on top of things. There was also several people who would come by to clear our empty plates and ask if we needed anything else.  It seemed very organized and like everyone was enjoying their work, which is something you don’t always see.  Nice atmosphere, too. Even though it was busy, it was not too loud. And although we sat on the first floor, they have two big screen TVs upstairs that show scenes from the streets of Paris. We may request the second floor next time.  I highly recommend and we can’t wait to go back.
Good food great ambience
Warmest waiter. Good mood.. great food. How nice place Le Sud,. I will be there in soon, again.
Wonderful
Great for roscoe village. Food is always flavorful. Service is great. It’s a must try if you live in the neighborhood.

I celebrated my PhD this evening in this gorgeous place. happy to tell that we had a magnificent evening and the restaurant was evidently the reason for that outstanding celebration. The team  helped in a sweet style, the cuisine was yummy and my buddies were very  joyful. We shall absolutely come back again for more celebrations. thanks very much.
I tried this place once with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I like the good character and flavorful food and drinks. I recommend this place.

This restaurant is obviously one of the tastiest restaurants in the region. Anytime I visit this place I am extremely pleased. They manage their very high  standard service and the highest level of meals  they give. You surely will enjoy this this restaurant. Very  recommended.
Excellent menu, great preparation, good options for vegetarians, fine service, really nice setting. Highly recommended for a special occasion and a great meal.
Super nice place!!!  Very good experience every single time! Awesome! Highly recommended!
Excellent food and service at a charming neighborhood spot.
One of my go to choices, great buzz, great food

What a delightful restaurant! From the moment you walk in, you know you are in for a treat. The place was decorated for the holidays-welcoming and trendy without being cold. You get the feeling right away you are going to have a good time. And then the amazing food- traditional yet modern. Our group had a nice sampling- chicken chasseur, bouillabaisse, steak frites, duck cassoulet and the fish of the day, branzino-all delish. Very accessible wine list, and of course, fab French desserts. We will all be going back again-soon!

This restaurant is the one I always prefer. I visit a lot of restaurants but to this restaurant I keep coming back again and again. The crew is very receptive and the cuisine they serve is so flavorful. I never decline to have a nice meal in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.
The meals and service were ahead of our expectations. I surely liked the atmosphere of this spot. Superb place to take the family out for dinner.
We loved each and every single thing we had here. We were especially blown away by the desserts!! So glad we made room for them. Great service, too. Can’t wait to come back
A nice neighborhood place with warm welcomes and nice food.  Selections lean to French bistro style without being slavish to the concept. We have always had first rate service here.
Food, ambiance, and service is all amazing!
Delicious food; professional and friendly service; nice atmosphere.
This place is awesome! Affordable prices, big dishes and the staff are constantly very friendly.

We've had several excellent meals here in the past and decided to return for their new prix-fixe. Unfortunately we were very disappointed. The room is wonderful, warm and inviting, and the service was excellent. Unfortunately, the food was a complete let down. The cassoulet was served in a warmish cast-iron container, but the contents were barely room temperature, and didn't taste remotely like a proper French cassoulet. The gnocchi are French style, and therefore different than usual Italian, and were described as being fluffy. Instead of fluffy and light, they were gummy and undercooked, and incredibly salty. Obviously, someone did not taste this in the kitchen. We enjoyed the wine, which is thoughtfully selected, and the chocolate mousse was delicious, and a good vehicle to make you hyperactive.  Since it's easy to spend $200 for two, I don't think we'll be returning soon.
Friendly service. The duck breast, rabbit stew and chicken liver pate were all excellent. Nice low-key stylish dining area.
Excellent food, great wine and fantastic ambiance.
Steak frites were fantastic, generously herb buttered but just enough to now overpower the steak. Delicious.
Food was great! The staff was amazing on Halloween! Appreciate the service and costumes on a slow night.

I had the steak frites. The steak was fantastic as was the sauce it came with but I have to say the fries were disappointing. Service was good too. I'd go back.

This place is my first choice place.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to this restaurant. when  I feel like having a superb supper, this place comes straight to my mind. extremely good and varied  food and a large list of dishes.courteous staff members, and nice atmosphere. Also, the expence is good. I tell about this spot with pleasure.
Great food and exceptional service

Can't say enough great things about our experience at Le Sud. As someone with over 30 years hospitality industry background, I can be a tough customer who notices everything, so I'm particularly thrilled will Le Sud. We didn't have a reservation and weren't really dressed for a fine dining experience, but fortunately it was early on a Wednesday night, so we had no issues getting a table. The staff couldn't have been more welcoming and accommodating. Friendly hostess; great waiter (Sean); amazing cocktails. (both Sean and two additional servers brought our drinks and helped clear our table. Great teamwork!); Food Runner was friendly and professional and made sure to crumb our table before marking us between courses. INCREDIBLE FOOD -- Grilled Octopus starter was fork tender. Scallops were beautifully  caramelized and both apps had numerous delicious and complex complimentary components; Bouillabaisse was a show stopper; Brown Butter Ice Cream was rich and intense. Definitely will return. Thanks!
Fantastic food, approachable atmosphere, great service!
Awesome food, friendly staff members, constantly good vibes. They charge fair pricing and the food quality is great. Kudos.
Great food and service. We will be going back.

We got there right when it opened on a weekday without a reservation.  Luckily, they had a table because the people started streaming in and before we knew it, it was packed!  We had celebratory drinks and two crab cakes.  Drinks were great and the crab cakes were creamy, crispy and tasty all at the same time.  Service was good.

Large party upstairs. Great room that let us mingle and be loud. Food was delicious (octopus was exceptional). A few from our party wanted to stay for an after dinner drink but the wait staff was not so keen to stay very long.
Our party of 3 had an amazing experience tonight. The food was wonderful as was the service from Sean. We dined al fresco and the only negative was the lack of lighting once nightfall arrived.

(Translated by Google) Local with nice atmosphere, I took the octopus (Spanish octopus) which was tender and tasty and the duck that I found very good, I also tried the mussels and without doubt they are among the best I've ever had, the cooking broth was superb. Paul, our waiter, was discreet, caring and sympathetic, he was genuinely sorry for not being able to please us when we requested an espresso, which is rather strange in a room of this level, this does not take away from the fact that it still remains a 5 star experience. Excellent food, french Mediterranean flair. Decor transports you to French countryside. Bartender Chris made our visit even better.

#update 8/9/19: we love this place and probably have been at least once a month for dinner and a few brunch and wine tastings. But since the new Chef has taken over things have changed and not really for the better. Last night was the second time under his stewardship and we felt that his tweaks to the menu that made the restaurant a hit, are misses. The flavors over power each other on the duck, and the steak frites has become pedestrian. We realize things change and menu items come and go in order to maintain the edge in the industry, but it seems like the subtle balance originally achieved here has been broken. Service is still excellent but the Management is different. Unfortunately we're going to have to wait out the changes for a while, hopefully it's just growing pains.  Excellent Restaurant in the heart of Roscoe village. From the Friendly greeters to the knowledgeable waitstaff, you'd think this place had been open for many years, but in a short time they have themselves a well oiled machine. We started with the charcuterie and salad and had Duck and Steak frites for our main meal. A tour of the French red wines by the glass accompanied our meals. I finished with a classic cocktail and my partner had some handmade gelato. Excellent spot for a date, or dinner with friends. Can't wait to go back.
Yum-O!
Great service, delicious food, lovely environment.
Love it.
This place is absolutely fantastic, the food and drinks are out of this world, and the service is impeccable!
What a gem! Great Sommelier.
A nust try

The new gem of Roscoe Village. Amazing food, great wine selection and staff that makes sure your experince is the best. Chris has been our waiter 2 out of the 3 times i have been there and his atrention to us is on point. Great suggetions always.

Excellent, simply excellent! Starters, pate in particular, blew our mind, not just taste buds. Our waiter, despite being in her job only for the second day, did a stellar job of a pro level. Wine selection is impressively well done and will satisfy even the picky connoisseurs. We had gnocchi and chicken as main dish and we can proudly say that even the French would say "délicieux".  We are so glad even Chicago now has a great French restaurant!

Thrilled to have a fine dining establishment in our neighborhood! Simon, the manager, went above and beyond to ensure we had a memorable dinner. Overall, the food was thoughtfully prepared and creative. I can’t say there was one standout dish, as every meal we ordered was tasty. Great menu, cute vibe and excellent service. Wonderful addition to Roscoe Village!

We failed to make a reservation and ended up sitting at the bar for the first 1 to 1.5 hrs. We ordered drinks and food at the bar with the knowledge that when a table opened up then we would be moved there. When a table became available we waited for another 30 minutes at which point we flagged down a waiter to see what happened to our food order (made > 1 hr before). He then informed us that it was never started.  I haven't really ever had problems with service before but we ended up waiting almost 2 hrs before actually receiving our food which felt longer than acceptable. The food wasn't so spectacular that I would feel okay waiting that long again. Would pass next time I'm in the area
Spanish octopus was phenomenal

Fresh, inviting space with excellent food. Very friendly staff. We shared the panisse frites which were served with a delicious aioli. Both the trout and the scallops were fabulous. Would recommend and will definitely be back myself.
Very good food and nice people
The food is phenomenal
Nice atmosphere, good food.

From the high ratings and reading about strong flavors, we were excited to come to this place for a little celebration. Overall, we left satisfied, and took plenty of photos (see attachments). However, we are on the fence on whether or not we would return again in the future.  First of all, we noticed that menu items on their website (specifically the bouillabaisse) was not on the menu at the restaurant. Nevertheless, we moved forward, and ordered appetizers: Seasonal cheese plate, Spanish octopus, and Niçoise Tartine (marinaded grilled tuna). The octopus was outstanding, the tuna good, however one of the cheeses (Scottish cheddar) had a strong mold-like taste. One server was kind to provide us with an extra slice of the creamy blue cheese, which was delectable.  For the main courses, we had the pan-roasted duck breast and the Mussels Provençal. The duck was flavorful, but chewy and fatty. The mussels dish was good, but was supposed to include prawns as per the menu description. Not sure why they were left off. Also the broth was a bit too salty to drink alone without the toasted bread.  The Cabernet ordered was silky, refreshing, and left the palate begging for more. But that was the problem (see photo). They poured so little of it and still charged $11. One has to wonder if this was an adequate “serving”.  During the evening, the service was phenomenal. You really had the impression the people working there were focused on taking care of you. Water glasses were filled promptly, and the dishes came out in a timely manner. That said, we only wished they offered better in terms of food and drink to bring us back.
Great place!
Food and service were excellent.  Sat outside on a lovely evening.  Highly recommend.
GREAT FRENCH RESTARAUNT! The escargot and octopus was great. The croquettes were so warm and crispy they were amazing. The steak and frittes were perfect.
A wonderful dinner.  Service, food and ambiance were perfect.  Thank you Matt from Trump for the recommendation!
The food and the service truly speaks for itself
Amazing food and so creative! The chef is a TALENT!  Excellent service, a must go to in Roscoe Village!

Cute place and convenient to Roscoe village where I live. I had heard good things and was eager to check it out. Unfortunately I found it a little dissapointing.  The food was underwhelming and I felt like a lot of items were over seasoned making it difficult to finish. I likely will not go back.
Excellent food and service. Scallops, steak frites and chevre lavender honey ice cream.
Loved the atmosphere  our waiter was very informative and the food was delicious wither exception of the green salad all stems I felt like I was eating dandelion weeds
Delicious southern French food!  Sandy and Bing have another amazing restaurant!
Great experience
Fantastic food served by an excellent staff at a good price.
Great atmosphere and tasty food. You should try their pork chop when you go there.
Absolutely spectacular. Cheese plate is well made. Steak Frites is done exactly as it should be. Service is terrific. Highest recommendation
Decor is great, food is fabulous, diversity of wine.  It was nice dinner place for good ambiance

Overall great experience for my family and I. Had my parents in town and it was my daughters first night out. Food, cocktails, wine suggestions, and service were all great.  Great addition to the neighborhood and hopefully we will go again. We got a reservation and would suggest that especially with it being new.  Only one suggestion to them, kids burger for my son the top bun is a little thick for a kid to eat effectively. I took a bite and it was great tasting so it’s just a little thing. You can’t go wrong with scallops, pork chop, duck, or the vanilla maple ice cream.
Everything was delicious and the service was delightful. Can't wait to go back!

Overall, great food, great ambiance, great service.  Made reservations for 7:30pm on a Saturday; definitely recommend reservations as it was busy. We had to wait a few minutes for our table, which was fine. For food, we had croquettes and a baguette to start. Scallops, the duck, and french fries for the main. And the Basque cake for dessert. We enjoyed all of it and would recommend those dishes.  For service, our water glasses were always filled and we generally didn't have a hard time getting our waiter's attention. I was most impressed when he immediately brought the wine list when our entrees came (we made a comment earlier that we'd switch to wine). I appreciate that we didn't even have to ask. And about a minute after that the manager walked by and asked if we knew what we wanted. He saw my dish and immediately gave me two recommendations and then brought me a taste of each of them without me asking.  While I live in walking distance to the restaurant I thought it was good enough that it would bring me to Roscoe Village if I didn't live here. I already have reservations to come back in a month for a family celebration.
Absoluetly gorgeous meal

My second time visiting and my expectations were surpassed once again.  The Foie Gras Tart was and still is incredible; packed full of flavour while not being overwhelming.  Hot tip: order the house baguette and put some of it on the warm bread.  I had the Split Pea Soup and Celeriac croquettes while my friend had the Steak Frites. Extremely flavourful and filling.  Can’t recommend enough. Like visiting France without paying for a flight.
Delicious.  The tart was amazing and best steak frits I've ever had
great food, outstanding service
Really enjoyed food and wine.
Great service, special occasion.
Little neck clams were awesome and the steak was delicious.
Really good home style French food
The service was great. The trout was very moist and the sauce was excellent.  The pea soup was very creamy with a nice tang to it.
Great Dinner for Restaurant week. All the family enjoyed a Very nice restaurant and meal.
Amazing service, ambiance, and food. Some of the best French food in Chicago. Highly recommend this place. The roasted duck was particularly delicious. Can’t wait to come back!

(Translated by Google) The whole experience was fantastic. The first recommendation would be to try to make a reservation so you do not have to wait long for a table. After that I have to say that the restaurant has a very good selection of food and drinks. They have very simple dishes but they also have much more daring and exquisite dishes. I have to say that the duck is terrific and I would recommend it to anyone. In terms of desserts, I would also recommend the chocolate mus or the sorbet.  (Original) Toda la experiencia estuvo fantástica. La primera recomendación sería intentar hacer una reservación para no tener que esperar mucho tiempo para una mesa. Después de eso tengo que decir que el restaurante tiene una muy buena selección de comida y bebidas. Tienen platos muy simples pero también tienen platos mucho más atrevidos y exquisitos. Tengo que decir que el pato está buenísimo y lo recomendaría a cualquiera. En cuestión de postres, también recomendaría el mus de chocolate o el sorbet.
Great find during Chicago Restaurant Week. Going back again soon!
Great food and service. Very professional

Attended restaurant week 2019 here. Staff was very attentive to us. They provided recommendations and combinations that would best complete our experience from their menu. Both the duck and roasted trout were excellent. Overall, very impressed. Will be returning in the future.

Great place for a private event! We had our office party here and the food was amazing. The staff was attentive and they were accommodating to everyones dietary needs. The wine and cocktails were unique and lovely. Everyone enjoyed the homemade break and we all had a variety of mains and desserts. Jackie was wonderful to work with. It is a fair price for wonderful food. We will be back

First time to try this french Mediterranean influence restaurant and I order duck, the food is excellent . I'm not a foodie but as Asian I really know what's a good duck should be it's not a Peking but it's tasty
Amazing French food with fantastic cocktails and one of the best, most balanced wine lists in the city.

This is a true gem. The atmosphere is suitable for a meeting,  date, anniversary you name it. Two bars to, the upstairs one a great place if you are solo dining. The staff is incredibly knowledgeable on the food and drink options. I was solo dining so my concentration being the small plates. First I started with a refreshing pilsner. This got my palette going. The foie gras was arguably the best I ever had. Even if you don't like liver, try it. You will love it. On to the octopus salad. Tender and loaded with flavor. The French fries finished off my dinner. I was full and satisfied. I enjoyed a wonderful Cabernet.  I look forward to going back with my wife so we can share some large plates. I finished everything with a cognac infused wine, recommended by the bartender. All this for less than $60. You can't go wrong. Enjoy.
Good food, great ambiance, great decor.
Food was wonderful: tried the duck, sturgeon, and chicken. The decor is well done, service was a bit spotty but good experience overall.
Great  food!!!Very  conversation  friendly. Charcuterie  was  a bit of heaven.  Escargot  were  different , but in a very  good way. Perfect  duck  breast!

I dined here for my Birthday in November 2018. This was a fantastic meal. I had the grilled escargot it was very non-traditional but delicious. The lavender glazed duck was so good I wanted to lick the plate. I can be picky, especially with duck and it was great. The wine list was nice, I had a delightful pairing offered to me by Mark, our server, who I've worked with in the past and who kept introducing me to everyone who worked there, including the owner who was incredibly sweet. I used to live next door to the woman who baked all of their bread- in house and I had previously worked with the management team. So many worlds collidided to make me feel right at home with some delicious contemporary French food in a very intimate and homestyle setting. Dessert was good; I enjoyed the cookies that came with the ice cream the most and was glad there were some gluten free options for others.  It did get quite loud being primetime on a Saturday night, although I didn't quite mind. We were on the second floor, so I'd imagine being on the first floor and/or going earlier/later in the night would be more manageable if the noise bothers you or you are hoping to have long conversation.  It was a great experience, the food was delicious and the service was excellent,  especially for how busy they were. The staff were all friendly and other guests seemed to be enjoying themselves as much as we were. I look forward to going back.
An amazing meal. One of the best discoveries of 2018. The price, the food, the ambiance, all hits.
Fantastic food!
The food was very good with a nice modern twist on some traditional French dishes. Our service was fantastic with a very knowledge waiter who did a great job navigating us through the delicious menu.
Great food
Great creative food great service Great restaurant
Very good
Excellent service and the food was outstanding. Everything we ordered featured flavor combinations that played off one another extremely well. Also enjoyed the wine and dessert wine selections.
South of France in the cold midwest.
So good it hurts!
Good food. Waiter was a bit too "touchy"

Awesome little spot in Roscoe Village! Cozy Vibes, and delicious french fair. My wife and I shared a bottle of wine a split a few dishes, i enjoyed the duck and boullbaise very much. Oh, and the service was on point!! Def worth checking out*
It is hitting the right spot.  The staff is really friendly and knowledgeable about the menu. Food was really tasty...love it!

My friend and I are always looking for new restaurants in the neighborhood, and I can't express what a gem this French restaurant is. The décor is classy. The customer service was top notch. Our waitress was amazing. She helped us navigate the menu. So many exotic flavors & so healthy! We started with bread and olive oil with herbs along with the Shrimp appetizer. The shrimps are hearty-sized and were perfectly seasoned. I would highly recommend these to start. Then we shared the roasted brussels sprouts, roasted carrots, and seared pumpkin fregola. The taste of all these dishes were so flavorful and so satisfying. They took some of my favorite dishes to the next level. The manager, Noel was very accommodating and helped us pick dessert. The Basque Cake was divine and different from any other dessert I have ever tasted in my life! I know I will be coming back because the exotic flavors and their taste set the crave. A great experience of local French cuisine overall. Magnifique!
Great food, and there were many other choices on the menu that looked tasty.  Great friendly service and a charming low key vibe.  A great addition to the neighborhood.
Great food great staff!!  only problem is it has already become THE place for a great meal ANY night of the week

A friend from LA wanted to celebrate her bday at @ le sud,come to find they wont take a resv but the hostess said u can walk in..really to give up a confirmed resv..so maybe someone walk in..Very disappointed!!!

Le sud now takes reservations! (Yeah) The place feels homey and the staff & manager are attentive. My husband is from France so we were excited to try this place and were not disappointed. We ordered the escargot, fois gras tarte, Quail dish , carrots and bouillabaisse.. with a lovely bottle of côtés de Rhône.  There is a kids menu and my 9 year old thought they had the best pasta! For dessert the vanilla maple ice cream and peach sorbet were a great finish..  they will definitly see  us again.
Neighborhood gem and also worth a trip. Cooking is excellent and the decor and ambiance is spot on. Will return many a time!!
Delicious.  Apple beet salad had wonderful dimensions.  Duck breast was superb!

Good but not quite there yet. Appetizers and wines were worthy of 4.5 stars, but the entrés did not shine. Overall, not a bad experience. We'll give it another chance in a few months and update accordingly.

This is  a review for Le Sud from my boss.....Outstanding, Five stars on every mark. Building was neat, outstanding set up, waitstaff were A1 and worth a great tip, food was best...best flavor, best presentation, best meal out in 15-20 years.
Both the food and ambiance at Le Sud were fantastic! This is a great new neighborhood gem that is worth a trip for anyone looking for a wonderful night out.
Excellent service. Very attentive and have good recommendations.
Oh my god, the pork chops. The pork chops, oh my god.
Great food and service!
One of my favorite meals of 2018 and new places in Chicago! Atmosphere, wait staff, wine selection and food were all exceptional.

Le Sud is a visually attractive restaurant with a great staff and excellent service.  The food was quite good overall.  A couple of dishes were just average, hence the one star off.  Definitely will come back to try more.
New French food locale, neighborhood spot. High quality chef prepared food, affordable pricing, wonderful beverage options.

Who eats mayonnaise with Fries? Oh yeah, the French. So oui, s'il vous plaît give me all the aioli with my fries at this French joint. Busy Friday night for this 2-week old restaurant but felt right at home. Love the attention to detail at this place - from the delicious food to the attentive service to the complimenting decor. Will be back very soon to try more of the menu.

Great food and excellent selection of French wines (even by the glass!).  The foie gras tart was out of this world. Very attentive, gracious staff.  Lovely ambience.  Definitely will be returning again and again.

A feast for the senses while maintaining touchs that will make Le Sud a neighborhood mainstay.  An exceptionally personal staff is the cherry on top a casual French brasserie that excels in presentation, flavor and friendliness.
Absolutely wonderful
Amazing new French restaurant in Roscoe Village!  Classic gems like roast chicken, loop de mer, and escargots!  Great wine list - affordable and good regional French wines. Go!
